<title>$30 Raspberry Pi computer module targets industrial uses</title>
<link>http://www.drivesncontrols.com/news/fullstory.php/aid/5314/$30_Raspberry_Pi_computer_module_targets_industrial_uses.html</link>
<description>A new version of the low-cost Raspberry Pi computer has been announced which is targeted at engineers developing embedded control systems. The Raspberry Pi 3 Compute Module (CM3) is based on the latest Raspberry Pi 3 architecture, with an ARM quad-core processor running at up to 1.2GHz, 1GB of LPDDR2 RAM and 4GB of on-board eMMC Flash storage. It has the same pin-out as the original Compute Module (CM1).</description>
