<item>
<title>NASA's glass gears have cracking potential</title>
<link>http://www.drivesncontrols.com/news/fullstory.php/aid/5302/NASA_s_glass_gears_have_cracking_potential.html</link>
<description>US researchers, led by scientists and engineers from NASAs Jet Propulsion Laboratory in California, are developing gears made out of special materials that that can act both as a metal and as a glass. The materials can operate efficiently without lubricants in extremely cold conditions, such as those found on the surface of planets and moons. They could also slash the cost of strain-wave gears used in applications such as robotics.</description>
<pubDate>Thu, 05 Jan 2017 05:00:00 GMT</pubDate>
