<title>Basic 100Mbit version of CC-Link IE will cut costs</title>
<link>http://www.drivesncontrols.com/news/fullstory.php/aid/5295/_91Basic_92_100Mbit_version_of_CC-Link_IE_will_cut_costs.html</link>
<description>CLPA  the CC-Link Partner Association  has announced an addition to its CC-Link IE protocol that will allow device vendors to add CC-Link IE compatibility to any product with a 100Mbit Ethernet port. The new version, known as CC-Link IE Field Network Basic  or Basic Mode  can be implemented on devices or master controllers using software alone, allowing it to be added to existing products without making any hardware modifications. CLPA says that this will reduce the cost of development and time-to-market significantly.</description>
