<link>http://www.drivesncontrols.com/news/fullstory.php/aid/5283/45mm-wide_twin-axis_servodrive_is__91world_92s_thinnest_92.html</link>
<description>The German motion engineer Stober has developed what it claims is the worlds narrowest multi-axis servodrive. The modular, rack-based SI6 system includes double-axis modules (2 x 5A) that are 45mm wide, resulting in six-axis systems that are 18cm wide, and 20-axis systems that are less than 50cm wide, including power supplies. The drives have a position, speed and current cycle time of 62.5µs.</description>
